@scenario_hash:1645eba89db8f651
Scenario: when a git tag of the form "vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH" is pushed to the shopsystem-templates repository, an OCI image is built and published to the canonical registry path "ghcr.io/dstengle/shopsystem-templates" with that version string as one of its image tags and "latest" as another tag — establishing the publication contract that bootstrap-via-docker-run depends on
  Given a tag named "v0.2.0" is pushed to the "main" branch of the shopsystem-templates source repository
  When the publication workflow associated with that tag push completes successfully
  Then the registry "ghcr.io" exposes an image manifest at the repository path "dstengle/shopsystem-templates" reachable by the image tag "v0.2.0"
  And the registry "ghcr.io" exposes an image manifest at the repository path "dstengle/shopsystem-templates" reachable by the image tag "latest" pointing to the same digest as the "v0.2.0" tag
  And both image tags can be pulled by an unauthenticated "docker pull" client because the package is published with public visibility
